<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy — Rwanda" %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

  <%# Header %>
  <div class="bg-container border border-primary rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
    <div class="bg-[#1a2744] px-8 py-6">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">PRIVACY POLICY</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 mt-1">Chancen Companion Mobile Application</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Chancen International Rwanda &middot; Kigali, Rwanda</p>
    </div>

    <%# Metadata table %>
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <tbody>
        <% [
          ["Entity",           "Chancen International Rwanda"],
          ["Effective Date",   "13 June 2026"],
          ["Last Updated",     "09 June 2026"],
          ["Review Cycle",     "Annual (or earlier if required)"],
          ["Next Review Due",  "13 June 2027"],
          ["Legal Framework",  "Law No. 058/2021 on the Protection of Personal Data and Privacy"],
          ["Regulator",        "Office of the Data Protection Office"],
        ].each_with_index do |(label, value), i| %>
          <tr class="<%= i.odd? ? 'bg-subtle' : 'bg-container' %> border-t border-primary">
            <td class="px-6 py-3 font-semibold text-primary w-48"><%= label %></td>
            <td class="px-6 py-3 text-secondary"><%= value %></td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <%# Supplement notice %>
  <div class="bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg px-6 py-4 mb-8 text-sm text-teal-900">
    <p><em>This document supplements the Chancen Companion Master Privacy Policy. In the event of any conflict, this <strong>Rwanda Privacy Policy Supplement</strong> shall prevail for users located in Rwanda.</em></p>
    <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-teal-700">Issued in compliance with Law No. 058/2021 and applicable guidance from the Data Protection Office.</p>
  </div>

  <%# Intro %>
  <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-secondary mb-8">
    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how personal data relating to <strong>users located in Rwanda</strong> is collected, used, disclosed and protected when you use the <strong>Chancen Companion mobile application</strong> (the "App"). It is issued in compliance with <strong>Law No. 058/2021 of 13/10/2021 on the Protection of Personal Data and Privacy in Rwanda</strong> and applicable guidance issued by the <strong>Office of the Data Protection Officer</strong>.</p>
  </div>

  <%# Sections %>
  <div class="space-y-8 text-sm text-secondary">

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">1. About the Chancen Companion App</h2>
      <p><strong>"Chancen Companion"</strong> refers to the mobile application operated by Chancen that allows users to access program information, including <strong>Income Share Agreement (ISA) participation details</strong>, communications, career resources, and financial literacy tools.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">The App supports students and graduates participating in Chancen education financing programs and related initiatives.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">2. Local Data Controller</h2>
      <p>For users located in Rwanda, the <strong>data controller responsible for your personal data</strong> is:</p>
      <div class="mt-3 bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg px-5 py-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-primary">Chancen International Rwanda</p>
        <p><strong>Company Reg. No.:</strong> RDB-261070719499480</p>
        <p><strong>Registered Address:</strong> KG 501 St, Kigali, Rwanda</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> companion@chancen.international</p>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3">As the <strong>Data Controller</strong>, Chancen International Rwanda determines how and why your personal data is processed when you use the App in Rwanda.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">The technical infrastructure supporting the App is operated by:</p>
      <div class="mt-3 bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg px-5 py-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-primary">Chancen International Services</p>
        <p>Registered in England and Wales &middot; Company No. 15299562</p>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3">Chancen International Services provides the <strong>technology platform and infrastructure</strong> that operate the App. However, Chancen International Rwanda remains responsible for personal data relating to users located in Rwanda.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">3. Data Protection Office Registration</h2>
      <p>Chancen International Rwanda is registered with the <strong>Office of the Data Protection Officer</strong> as a Data Controller and/or Data Processor under Law No. 058/2021.</p>
      <p class="mt-2"><strong>Data Protection Office Registration Number:</strong> [Registration Number]</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">4. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>We may collect and process the following categories of personal data:</p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary mt-4 mb-1" style="color: #0d9488;">4.1 Identity Information</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2">
        <li>Full name</li>
        <li>Identification or student identification details</li>
        <li>Date of birth (where required)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-semibold mt-4 mb-1" style="color: #0d9488;">4.2 Contact Information</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2">
        <li>Email address</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-semibold mt-4 mb-1" style="color: #0d9488;">4.3 Account Information</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2">
        <li>Username and login credentials</li>
        <li>Account activity within the App</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-semibold mt-4 mb-1" style="color: #0d9488;">4.4 ISA Program Information</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2">
        <li>ISA participation status</li>
        <li>Repayment obligations</li>
        <li>Payment history</li>
        <li>Balance estimates</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-semibold mt-4 mb-1" style="color: #0d9488;">4.5 Device and Technical Information</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2">
        <li>Device type and operating system</li>
        <li>App usage data and log information</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-semibold mt-4 mb-1" style="color: #0d9488;">4.6 Communications Data</h3>
      <p>When you contact support, provide feedback, or interact with the App's AI chatbot, we may collect the information you share in those communications — including messages, questions, and responses. These interactions help us respond to requests and improve our financial literacy tools. Where possible, we anonymise or remove identifying information before using it for analysis or product improvement.</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li>Messages and chatbot interactions within the App</li>
        <li>Support requests or feedback</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-3">Chancen collects <strong>only the personal data necessary</strong> to provide the App and support ISA program participation.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">5. Lawful Basis for Processing</h2>
      <p>We process personal data on the following legal bases under Law No. 058/2021:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li><strong>To provide App services and manage ISA participation;</strong> Contractual necessity</li>
        <li><strong>To comply with applicable laws and regulatory requirements;</strong> Legal obligation</li>
        <li><strong>To improve App functionality, security, and user experience;</strong> Legitimate interests</li>
        <li><strong>Where required, including for specific communications or optional features.</strong> Consent</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">6. How We Use Personal Data</h2>
      <p>Your personal data may be used for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li>Providing access to the Chancen Companion App</li>
        <li>Displaying ISA participation and repayment information</li>
        <li>Managing user accounts</li>
        <li>Communicating program updates and notifications</li>
        <li>Providing career, employment, and financial literacy resources</li>
        <li>Maintaining platform security and preventing fraud</li>
        <li>Improving App functionality and user experience</li>
        <li>Complying with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">7. ISA Account Data</h2>
      <p>The App allows users to view information relating to their <strong>Income Share Agreement (ISA)</strong> participation, including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li>Estimated ISA balance</li>
        <li>Payment history</li>
        <li>Repayment status</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3">This information is derived from Chancen's internal systems, including its <strong>Data Warehouse</strong>. Balance information <strong>may not always reflect real-time updates and should be treated as an informational estimate only</strong>. For official balance confirmations, please contact Chancen International Rwanda directly.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">8. Data Sharing and Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>Personal data may be shared with trusted third parties where necessary to operate the App and deliver Chancen services:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li>Cloud infrastructure providers</li>
        <li>Technology service providers supporting the App</li>
        <li>Payment processing partners (where applicable)</li>
        <li>Legal or regulatory authorities were required by law</li>
        <li>AI Technology Partners (e.g., OpenAI): We take steps to remove your name and ID before sharing chatbot interactions, so the partner can generate a response without being able to identify you.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3"><strong>We do not sell your information to third parties.</strong> All providers are required to process personal data in accordance with appropriate security and confidentiality obligations.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">9. Data Transfers Outside Rwanda</h2>
      <p>To operate the App, some personal data may be processed or stored outside Rwanda — for example, by Chancen International Services in the United Kingdom or by international technology providers.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">Where cross-border transfers occur, Chancen implements <strong>appropriate safeguards</strong> in accordance with Law No. 058/2021, including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li>Contractual data protection obligations with service providers</li>
        <li>Secure cloud infrastructure and encryption</li>
        <li>Technical and organisational security measures</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">10. Data Security</h2>
      <p>Chancen takes reasonable <strong>administrative, technical, and physical measures</strong> to protect personal data from unauthorised access, loss, misuse, or disclosure, including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li>Encryption of sensitive data</li>
        <li>Restricted access controls</li>
        <li>Secure infrastructure and monitoring systems</li>
        <li>Internal policies governing data protection</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">11. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li>Provide App services</li>
        <li>Support ISA program participation</li>
        <li>Comply with legal or regulatory obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3">Retention periods vary depending on the nature of the data and applicable legal requirements. If you delete your account through the App settings, we will delete your App-related personal data within 30 days unless retention is required by law.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">12. Your Rights Under Rwandan Data Protection Law</h2>
      <p>Under <strong>Law No. 058/2021 on the Protection of Personal Data and Privacy</strong>, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2 mt-2">
        <li>Be informed about the use of your personal data</li>
        <li>Access your personal data</li>
        <li>Object to the processing of your data</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate or misleading personal data</li>
        <li>Request deletion of inaccurate or misleading personal data</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent at any time where processing is based on consent</li>
        <li>Human Review: request a human review of any important Chancen ISA-related information generated by our AI chatbot</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3">Chancen International Rwanda has procedures in place to help users exercise all of these rights.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">13. How to Exercise Your Rights</h2>
      <p>To exercise your data protection rights, please contact Chancen International Rwanda using the details in Section 16. Requests should include enough information for us to verify your identity and locate your data.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">We will aim to respond <strong>within 30 days</strong>, subject to verification and the complexity of the request.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">14. How to Complain</h2>
      <p>If you are not satisfied with how Chancen International Rwanda handles your personal data, you may file a complaint with the <strong>Office of the Data Protection</strong>:</p>
      <div class="mt-3 bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg px-5 py-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-primary">Office of the Data Protection</p>
        <p><strong>Website:</strong> dpo.gov.rw</p>
        <p><strong>Address:</strong> 21 KG 7 Ave, Kacyiru, A&amp;P Building, Ground Floor, Kigali</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">15. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>Chancen may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in technology, legal requirements, or App functionality. Updated versions will be made available within the App.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">Where changes are material, we will notify you through the App or via email. Continued use of the App following such notification constitutes acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">16. Contact Information</h2>
      <p>For questions about this Privacy Policy or how your personal data is processed, please contact:</p>
      <div class="mt-3 bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg px-5 py-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-primary">Chancen International Rwanda</p>
        <p><strong>Address:</strong> KG 501 St, Kigali, Rwanda</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> companion@chancen.international</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <p class="mt-10 text-xs text-subdued text-center">Confidential &middot; companion@chancen.international</p>
</div>
